        "content": "<p>Is there a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#SeminormedAddGroup\">SeminormedAddGroup</a> where the image of the norm is (similar enough to) the set {0, 1+1, 1+1/2, 1+1/3, 1+1/4, ...}?</p>",
        "id": 530533890,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1753356178
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(where \"similar enough to\" means that it's order-isomorphic and 0 is still not the limit)</p>",
        "id": 530534255,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1753356275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>ℕ →₀ ZMod 2</code> with <code>‖f‖ = 1 + 1 / (1 + inf {n|f n ≠ 0})</code></p>",
