    {
        "content": "<p>so i wanted to prove that the nhds 0 is generated by { y : |y| &lt; |x| } for x such that |x|&gt;0 but i couldn’t rule out this case (following mathlib’s convention i would prove it in the highest generality, since this is obviously true for fields)</p>",
